SIMPLE: fondness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fondness
<hw>Fond"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state
of being fond; foolishness.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> <qex>Fondness</qex> it were for any, being free,⟦br⟧
To covet fetters, though they golden be.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Doting affection; tender liking; strong appetite,
propensity, or relish; <as>as, he had a <ex>fondness</ex> for
truffles</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> My heart had still some foolish <qex>fondness</qex> for thee.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Attachment; affection; love; kindness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fondon</ent>⟦br⟧
